title: For Sale:  S&W SW1911E
postcontent: The Smith & Wesson® SW1911 E-Series Semi-Auto Pistol uses the same John Browning design as the standard-issue .45 caliber M1911 sidearm used by the United States Armed Forces from 1911 to 1985, tough with modern features you would only expect on a custom gun. Smith & Wesson added deep fish-scale scallops on the front and rear gripping surfaces of the stainless steel slide to provide an aggressive non-slip grip for manual cycling. The frontstrap of the grip frame and the mainspring housing are also aggressively checkered for a secure grasp, and the top of the slide is full-length grooved with S&W's classic revolver barrel-rib pattern. The wooden grip panels are figured with an attractive fish-scale pattern that matches the slide-grip surfaces. Smith & Wesson also refined the internal mechanism of the SW1911 E-Series Semi-Automatic Pistol for enhanced reliability. A patent-pending S&W Model 1911 trigger was engineered that allows the trigger to be precisely hand-fitted instead of simply installed during the assembly process without adding undue expense to the process. The new trigger eliminates excessive vertical and front-to-back freeplay in the frame slot, providing shooters with a precisely fitted trigger, equal to or better than a lot of custom triggers. The trigger also has an adjustable setscrew for overtravel. The E-Series 1911 features an extra heavy-duty external extractor and a redesigned ejection port to guarantee reliable case ejection with the many varieties of ammo available today. Continued features from the previous SW1911 line include a full-length steel recoil-spring guide rod, open-end guide rod cap, and a visual loaded-chamber window at the rear top of the barrel hood. The humpbacked beavertail safety cups the hammer to keep it from biting the shooter's hand, and the manual thumb safety has an extended combat-type lever. The operating features–beavertail safety, manual safety, magazine release button, and slide release lever–are a contrasting matte black, as are the steel 3-dot front and rear sights. The Smith & Wesson SW1911 E-Series Semi-Auto Pistol comes with two 8-round magazines with buttpads. Manufacturer model #: 108482. Recoil is very manageable. Strong, planted grip with checkered wood grips means that the recoil does not snap or kick...it is more of a "push" and really cushions the recoil.  Even shooters accustomed to a lighter round will be able to handle it very easily.
Sharp looking grips have full checkering for a tight grip.
Double stack, high capacity magazine.Field stripping is a snap, using Beretta’s sure-footed, quick lever takedown that easily removes the slide from the frame. From there, the recoil spring, guide tube and barrel are easily removed.
Unbeatable Taurus lifetime warranty (transferrable to all subsequent owners).Comes with factory box.
 
** The features, fit and finish of its more expensive cousins that it easily rivals. Note the absence of machine marks, a characteristic of higher end firearms.
 
 
Carry options: De-cock the hammer by thumbing the safety lever all the way down and carry it chambered, hammer down, off safe for a first double action shot.  You can also keep the safety on, then thumb it off with and have a first double action shot.  If you are a 1911 fan, then you can also carry cocked and locked which is the hammer cocked, safety on with a first shot being single action.
